Economic and reputational risks due to accidents and injuries 

Accidents involving employees could lead to operational disruptions and reputational damage, potentially slowing down company 

operations. If such incidents affect employee health and safety, the Company could face legal claims, compensation costs, and 

sanc tions for non -compliance with regulations and organisation systems (OMC 231). An unsafe working environment could reduce the 

Company’s appeal to potential investors and diminish employee motivation, leading to higher turnover rates. 

