▪ Monitoring the adequacy, updates, and effectiveness of the 231/2001 System; 

▪ Monitoring the application of the Code of Ethics by the parties concerned by applying internal  audit plans; 

▪ Reporting any significant violations of the Code of Ethics; 

▪ Suggesting periodic reviews of the Code of Ethics. 

▪ Ensuring compliance with the Anti -Corruption and Anti -Bribery Policy; 

o Internal Audit: 

▪ Verifying compliance with the Code of Ethics. 

